HEADWORD: Lysimachia
<hw>Lysimachia</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a cosmopolitan genus
of plants, including some of the loosestrifes, found in damp or swampy
terrain having usually yellow flowers; they are inclined to be
invasive.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Lysimachia</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
